clue: "Circus Sideshow", completed in 1888, was this artist's first night painting using the pointillist technique

response: Seurat

clue: He painted "Night Fishing at Antibes" just before the outbreak of World War II

response: Picasso

clue: In Rousseau's "Sleeping Gypsy", a full moon hangs in the night sky while this animal catches the scent of the title figure

